            },
            {
              "label": "(b)",
              "token": "b",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "For a supplemental plan or a waiver that proposes to use alternative transportation for one or more routes not previously included in a supplemental plan or a waiver, an explanation of why the school district has determined that the use of alternative transportation for the route is necessary. The applying school district adequately demonstrates that any expenses incurred in excess of subsection",
              "subsections": []
            },
            {
              "label": "(c)",
              "token": "c",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "For a waiver request that proposes to use public transportation for secondary school students, an explanation of how:",
              "subsections": [
                {
                  "label": "(A)",
                  "token": "A",
                  "kind": "alpha_upper",
                  "text": "The use of public transportation qualifies for approved transportation costs under ORS 327.033",
                  "subsections": []
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "(5)",
          "token": "5",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "The State Board of Education may approve a supplemental plan or a waiver request to use alternative transportation and to provide reimbursement for costs incurred in providing alternative transportation only when:",
          "subsections": [
            {
              "label": "(a)",
              "token": "a",
              "kind": "alpha_lower",
              "text": "The projected approved transportation costs under subsection",
              "subsections": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "(6)",
          "token": "6",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "Notwithstanding subsection",
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(7)",
          "token": "7",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "When the State Board of Education approves a supplemental plan or waiver request to use alternative transportation and provides reimbursement for costs incurred in providing alternative transportation, the approved supplemental plan or waiver shall be effective for two years from the date of approval. of this section, a school district that, prior to January 1, 2024, had been receiving reimbursement for costs incurred in providing transit passes under a supplemental plan or a waiver shall continue to receive reimbursement under the terms and conditions the school district was receiving reimbursement prior to January 1, 2024, unless the State Board of Education and the school district agree otherwise.",
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(8)",
          "token": "8",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "Notwithstanding subsections",
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(9)",
          "token": "9",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "Nothing in this section prevents a school district from providing alternative transportation in addition to otherwise required transportation when no reimbursement is sought for costs incurred in providing the alternative transportation. [1991 c.780 7; 2023 c.524 2] Note: The amendments to",
